                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13017653" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 8 Apr 2011 21:23:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to avoid storing DecoratedKeys with null key (which are generated by getRangeSlice) in the key cache.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13017667" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 8 Apr 2011 21:41:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why not do that in cacheKey directly to be sure we don&apos;t miss places ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13021088" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 18 Apr 2011 16:20:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Because attempting to cache a DK that is really just a token is a semantic error that we shouldn&apos;t just paper over.  v2 adds an assert to make that clear.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13021097" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 18 Apr 2011 16:46:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13021104" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 18 Apr 2011 16:56:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13021154" author="hudson" created="Mon, 18 Apr 2011 18:07:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.7 #439 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/439/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/439/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    avoid caching token-only decoratedkeys&lt;br/&gt;
patch by jbellis; reviewed by slebresne for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2416&quot; title=&quot;NullPointerException in CacheWriter.saveCache()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-2416&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-2416&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
